  "texts": [
    "This approach studies and represents text with pre-trained models, namely models that have been pre-trained on large datasets.",
    "Typically, the BERT model comes in two sizes: BERTBASE and BERTLARGE [20].",
    "The BERTBASE model consists of 12 encoder layers (transformer blocks), with a hidden size of 768, 12 self-attention heads, and a total of 110 million parameters.",
    "On the other hand, the BERTLARGE model has 24 encoder layers, a hidden size of 1,024, 16 self-attention heads, and a total of 340 million parameters.",
    "The study employs the BERTBASE model, as depicted in Figure 7."
